\v 23 but¦119640 each in his¦119654 own turn: first¦119645 \nd Messiah¦119646\nd* will be leading, then when he \add returns\add*, those who belong to him.
\v 24 Then the end¦119657 will come when he hands over the kingship to \nd God¦119666\nd* the Father after he's destroyed all rule, and all authority¦119677 and power¦119679,
\v 25 because¦119681 he must reign¦119683 until¦119684 he's defeated all his¦119695 enemies¦119690.\x + \xo 15:25: \xt Psa 110:1.\x*
